data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Henderson, NV Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
On Saturday the 25th of May, I needed to replace 3 hinges on a couch headrest. I live now in Tennessee and was met with negative service in Murry, KY and how they are privately owned and could not honor my coverage on my couch that I bought 5 years ago. I called directly to Stephanie location in Henderson where I bought my couch and OMG.... Elizabeth Overdorff was absolutely 5 star the best!! I have worked in Customer Service profession for over 35 years and Elizabeth did the crossing of the T's and the dotting of ever eye (i) by sticking to the golden rule of Customer Service... Yes we can, Yes I will and Yes I will get that shipped out immediately. Today is Wednesday May 29th and my parts arrived as promised!!!!!! I cannot say enough about the professionalism that is extended and believed in with this location in Henderson, NV. Danielle hoped on the line today and ensured that she will get the additional part needed.. Thank you Elizabeth and Danielle.. True examples of Fantastic, caring Customer Service... "I REALLY HOPE CORPORATE RECOGNIZES YOU BOTH"...Thank You, Thank You, and Thank you again. Donna Jean Newport... yep Tennessee "I'm going fishing"

We walked in Ashley’s, we originally knew what we wanted. We found the couches we were looking for as we had purchased them before at another Ashley’s location but our order was cancelled due to them not having the set of couches, in the middle of the purchase a lot of confusion spiked between me and the sales associate mainly because I was confused as why this couches were for sale when my original order was cancelled due to them not having this couches, long story short we bought the couches again, Danielle the manager was able to fix couple issues which we really appreciate she was very patient and nice, moving forward we didn’t want to pay delivery fee of $250 because I have a big truck we were told by the sale associate that upon picking up our couches at the warehouse they were not going to be wrap with plastic or anything, we brought our own wrapping to only find out when they gave us the couches that they were completely wrapped the issue with that is that they told us to inspect the couches but you can only inspect the couches with the wrap and plastic around them, you can’t really inspect the actual couches we figured that because the plastic was not ripped the couches should probably be fine inside so we took them home and when we put it in our living room we unpackaged them to our surprise every single couch had a dirt stain, mainly the ottoman with that being said we are disappointed because we know how extremely careful we were to unwrapped them and now we have brand new couches that we haven’t even sat on and they’re all dirty. With that being said we are pretty unsatisfied. Update! Thanks to management over at Ashley’s our problem was fixed , they did take full responsibility in making our couches look amazing! And they really showed they wanted to make us feel good about our purchase! We understand not everything is perfect All the time but we are thankful they fixed the issue we had. Will definitely keep buying from Ashely’s again for the rest of our home, five star for the customer service!

The act of purchasing was good, scheduled delivery of a love seat, couch and table like 3 weeks out. Night before delivery I got rid of the couches that I had. Delivery day they show up with the love seat and table. Driver said the couch was on backorder. I called Ashley and they said no it is not it is at the warehouse, can we call you back? We will try and get it out to you. Never got a call back. Called just now (Sunday morning) just like when I called Saturday they act like they don't know what's going on. Put me on hold and tell me I have to wait a week almost to get the couch. I have a family of 5, 2 spots to sit. I asked why can't they get it to me tomorrow since my couch was at the warehouse but didn't get delivered? I was told the trucks are preloaded 2 days before and they can't accommodate me. I do not recommend. Terrible service once you buy their product. They don't care and will not even call you back. No integrity at all. I will never buy from them again. Oh yeah delivery charge is like $180 and can't get your items to you. Will never buy from them again. UPDATE: After posting this someone reached out and asked me how we can fix this, anyway they were able to get my couch delivered 1 day earlier and said they would deduct the delivery charge from my order. I will post if that happens... I read their reply and responded accordingly..

Editing my review down to one star. My table came 10/31/23 missing hardware so they had to take it back since it was unable to be assembled. Also showed up with three damaged chairs. They responded that they would have it replaced within 24 hrs. They reached out to me and gave me a delivery date for 9 days later. Not ideal but I accepted. Today is finally the day I should be getting the rest of my furniture. I don’t know why I’m surprised, but I still didn’t get it all. They showed up with the table and two out of the three chairs with no explanation as to why I’m not getting all the stuff I purchased. Just found out that they don’t have it in the warehouse and have no idea when I will even get it. Asked if I could have one from the store I bought it from so I can complete my formal dining room set by thanksgiving and was told they almost guarantee the store won’t let me as then the store wouldn’t have a complete model set for the showroom. I guess have a complete set to sale more of, even though there are none at the warehouse, is more important than giving the customer the chair they already paid for.

We just had the best experience buying our furniture for our new place in our new city. We were ready for this to be a whole adventure and even talked about keeping a nice attitude and to just communicate if we got overwhelmed. Well, the very first place we visited was Ashley Furniture and it turns out this didn’t even have to be overwhelming at all. Mark Nachman promptly greeted us at the door, took a bit of his time to explain how things ran in the store and made it a point to give us our time to look around by ourselves. We do not like it when the sales representatives are right there by us and we can’t freely discuss things with each other. He was not only knowledgeable and professional but also kind and so respectful. Then everything got even better when we got with the Sales manager , Danielle Meek. Danielle totally made my day with her willingness, kindness and happy approach while helping us out. We are done with our shopping and it was not a hassle at all!!! Thank you guys!

I ordered a sectional from Ashley Furniture in Henderson on 6/27/22. The order was supposed to be delivered in 6 weeks but wasn’t delivered until almost 9 weeks (after multiple calls). My husband accepted the delivery but the sectional we received was entirely entirely different than the one we ordered in store. My husband works till late in the evening and I am busy with school. Calling them doesn’t help as you are placed on hold for hours. My husband also didn’t want to wait another 8 weeks but I was not happy because it was not what I wanted nor ordered. We finally went there in person to talk to them (it’s been a week) to tell them that these are different couches and they told me that their policy is 3 days and only for damage/defective items. The item was neither damaged nor defective but we received something other than what we ordered. The 3 day window was in the fine print but we didn’t read that nor did anyone accuse us verbally of a 3 day window. We talked to the office manager Alicia and the store manager Sabrina but they said they can’t do anything. Initially, they kept insisting that the incorrect sectional was, in fact, what we had ordered in the first place. Then they agreed the wrong sectional was sent to us. After they noticed the three day window was up, they kept referring to that. I am making payments for something I did not order and I am stuck with it. As we were about to leave, the office manager Alicia and store manager Sabrina started laughing loudly at something. Could’ve been anything, but obviously I didn’t find anything amusing in our interaction. I am just angry because I am spending my hard earned money on this couch every month but its not even what I wanted. They said we can try calling corporate but we know nothing will happen. This was the Mall ring circle location near Galleria mall. Just wanted to vent and let everyone know about it. I will never shop from there as they are not honorable. It was a bait and switch. I am attaching the pictures in store and the one on their tablet that they showed us versus what they gave us. The quality and design are subpar to the one we liked. Be careful of where you spend your money and just because it’s a big name-brand store doesn’t mean they are honorable with keeping their word. I just wanted to spread the word.

I don’t even know where to begin. We purchased a 5 item bedroom set January 1st 2022 and we still don’t have it all. It took 6 months to even start receiving the pieces we ordered (We were told 5-6 weeks at the time of purchase.) 2 out of the 4 pieces we’ve received so far are damaged and we’re still waiting on a tech to come out and look at them. We were supposed to receive our last piece last week and the delivery drivers never showed. I confirmed date and time 3 times and they still didn’t come. We went into the store last night to speak to a sales manger (Sabrina DiBlasi) because you can never get correct information by phone. We were told she would be with us in a few minutes. We sat there and watched Sabrina test out a mattress with another employee while we were standing there waiting for 5-10 minutes. Like, are you kidding me?! We couldn’t believe her behavior. Sabrina DiBlasi has been giving us the run around every time we visit the store. It’s unfortunate the quality and customer service is so bad because when you walk into the store everything looks so beautiful. Do not shop at Ashley Furniture! We will never purchase anything there ever again!

Worst place to purchase furniture!!!! I purchased several pieces (couch, TV stand, coffee table, 2 shelves, sofa table) on Nov 30 2021. In Feb I received the couch and tv stand. As of April 24 2022 still waiting for the rest. I was informed I would receive coffee table in March, shelves in April and the rest in May. March came and went so after being on hold for 3 hours with the store I went to the store. The manager seemed to be helpful and had the girls look up my purchase. He proceeded to tell I'd have coffee table and shelves by mid April and did give 400 store credit (not very useful with their prices) so I did and exchange of sofa table and his credit for a dining room table. At that time I was still getting my delivery in April and dining room would be July. Well I never received April delivery as they called the other day to say we will not be getting anything in April but now May and rest in July. Why would anyone want to wait 8 months for furniture. Go anywhere else but Ashley furniture!!!!

Store continually blames Covid for their ineptitude. Manager of the Henderson , NV store, John S. when calling to follow up on our April delivery date, he blamed production for it now being moved back to mid May. This is interesting to me because , he called production in March and said the delivery would be in April. Declining to discuss my disappointment and continuing to use the excuse of COVID, John declined to discuss the matter further saying we have already discussed this is March. In 3 different occasions in the conversation, he said I do not want to rehash what we previously discussed, even though this was a new problem. He stated that if we were that unhappy and production was not completed by 5/13/22, he would send a truck to pick up the 2 pieces of the 3 piece sectional we purchased which I said did not make sense to me. He then , what do you expect me to do? At this point, I firmly stated in a loud voice, get it delivered be fore May 13th as we will not be home as we are getting married. I then hung up on him. If there was a scale of 1 - 10, 10 being best, he would be a negative 99.

ZERO stars. After waiting 2.5 months to receive my items (which I understand due to Covid delays) the day of delivery only 3 of my 4 items arrived and 2 of those 3 items came damaged. Their policy is that if your items come damaged the first time, you are then considered "VIP" and they will now check the items for damage before they arrive. How is that VIP treatment and not regular treatment??? They rescheduled my delivery for the next week but during those few days I received numerous calls and emails changing my items and delivery date. One minute all three items would be coming on a certain day, the next I would be receiving partial deliveries. I had to speak to a manger in order to get everything resolved and called customer service at least 10 times while waiting on hold an average of 30 minutes each time. My delivery time was supposed to be from 10:45 to 1:45. Got a call at 11am that the truck was late and it would come at 2:10. At 2:45 I had to call to get an update as they still didn't come. I was then told 3:45. I called back at 4:15 because they STILL hadn't arrived and they finally showed up at 5pm. HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE AND I WILL NEVER SHOP AT ASHLEY FURNITURE AGAIN IN LIFE. Ashley is incompetent, disorganized, and they do not care about their customers.

I used to absolutely love Ashley furniture. After my last experience I will NEVER buy another piece of furniture from here again! We spent almost 2k on a couch from them and it broke a month after recieving it. We could not get ahold of anyone over the phone at the store or corporate. My husband finally got tired of trying and drove down to the store. They said "we will have a technician call you", that took a couple weeks and a couple months later the technician comes to the house. The technician looks at the couch and says "yep its broken, we'll get you a new one". He calls the factory or somewhere and they said they have it in stock, so he tells us someone will get ahold of us to set up a delivery in the next couple of days. A couple weeks later my husband tries calling again, this time his number goes straight to a voice message that doesn't give him any options to talk to someone. The voice message says we will get our couch in FEBRUARY... FEBRUARY! These F'ers! Now we can't get ahold of anyone at the store again. And we have to sit on our brand new broken couch for 4 months before they decide to bring us a new one. DO NOT BUY FROM HERE! LITERALLY GO ANYWHERE ELSE! YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED!

I’ve been looking for a bedroom set for a while. Saw a set in an advertisement that Ashley mailed me. I waited and searched other outlets to be sure of the set I wanted. I decided to purchase from Ashley just to try the experience and compare to RC Willey. I arrived President’s day weekend (2/15). Greeted within 30 seconds of entering by Tim Watkins. He immediately apologized for no one greeting me sooner. Let me say Tim is an outstanding salesman. I thought for sure he had been working there for years but he had only started a few weeks before my appearance. He allowed me to browse the area and search for what I’m looking for. Granted I already knew what I wanted but I had to be sure. After much time, I chose my bedroom set and opened an in store credit to receive the promo. Tim did a great job explaining every. I felt like he was my personal salesman and I had known him for years - he made me that comfortable. I’m only giving 4 stars due to the store not Tim. The other salesman waited and conversed unprofessionally. If I didn’t get Tim I’d probably leave. Also I was hungry, at RC Willey I remember popcorn being available for customers. I probably would have purchased more than a bedroom set but after I made my decision to purchase I became hungry. I’ll shop here again and hopefully schedule an appointment with Tim. Also Tim followed up as promise on my delivery status. Update: My order didn't arrive. on 2/21/20, I called the corporate number and was redirected to the store. The call center for corporate was very unprofessional. The manager at the store answered the phone and told me my delivery has changed to 2/28. Said it changed because they couldn't get a hold me. Asked if I received a text. I said no. She said it must have gone to the second number on file and she will remove the second number. (The second number I was told was mandatory to have on file). Luckily I was already planning for two deliveries; the mirror on the 28th.I didn't argue just replied that date will work - especially since they already scheduled it. 2/25 & 2/26, I finally got those texts about my delivery schedule and so did the second number on file too. The store has been reduced to 3 stars. Read a review that said due to the type of payment method (i.e. cash, google pay) you can get a better deal. I was told if I open an account I can get the best deal.

The two stars are for the staff that I dealt with starting from the salesperson and all customer service reps at Ashley’s in Henderson, NV. They were all very friendly and professional. My girlfriend and I financed a 14 piece living room set from Ashley’s in early January (about a month before our move-in date). After about a week we decided to change the lamps so I called and took care of it. No problems there. A week after that I receive a call explaining that our lamps are backordered and won’t reach us until about a week after we move in. No biggie. Another week goes by and our accessories are also back ordered, they will arrive two weeks after I move in. Still not a big deal, we can live without those items, the important stuff is the couch and tables. Those items showed up on time and were assembled in a timely manner, no complaints. Fast forward a week and half, I get a call that our lamps are out for delivery. I receive a package in the mail, only to discover it was the accessories. Really not a big deal, slightly disappointed because I want to see my living come together but ultimately not the end of the world. I called to make sure Ashley’s was aware I was sent the accessories instead of the lamps. They were confused and weren’t of much help. So I waited for the lamps. Today I was left a voicemail that my lamps have arrived at the store and rather than them being delivered I would have to go pick them up. Excited about finally getting my lamps I thought it wasn’t too much trouble to drive the 25 minutes to pick them up. Upon arrival they went back to grab the boxes. When the employee came back she was only holding one box, so I inquired about the other box. She checked her computer to find out they only ordered one. Then explained that she wasn’t sure if it would be sent to my home or if I had to pick it up. I was confused as to why I would have to pick anything up in the first place, let alone two lamps at separate times which were already late to begin with? I was then told that they will ship today or tomorrow so I will likely be able to pick them up OR they will reach my house by sat/mon. She was unable to give me a definite answer as to how I would receive my second lamp. Once I got home the lamp was chipped. I called to let the store know. And they were too busy to speak with me. The customer service rep told me that all exchanges would be done in store so I could drive back to the store to set up and exchange. Now I will have to drive to the store to pick up my second lamp, then set up an exchange and likely have to drive back to pick up my replacement lamp. None of this makes sense considering I paid for delivery. I’d like to note that I’m happy with all of my furniture thus far. It all looks nice and is very comfortable. ***Update**** John, the manager of the store called to apologize and sort out the situation. He took full ownership and was very polite. New lamps have now arrived and neither of them are broken. My living room is now complete.

Bad customer service, I bought a sofa and they told me it would be ready for pick up in two days which would be on Wednesday, I called Wednesday just to make sure that it was there before driving to the MLK location since it's a 30 min drive from my house. They said there was a delay and that I had to pick it up on Friday, I called Friday again to make sure and they said there was another delay that it would be ready on Saturday, I called Saturday and they said that it wouldn't be ready for pick up until the 26 of December when I bought it cash on December 2. At that point I got upset and frustrated and told the woman on the phone that how was it possible that I had to wait 1 month for something that I purchased and was supposed to be ready in two days and she told me to drive to the store to get my money back so I did . Never going there again.

I will never buy anything from here again! From start to finish, my experience here has been a complete joke. I walked in the store and one of the workers said they would help us find a mattress but would be right back. He never came back. We decided what mattress we wanted and there were no workers to be found except for one elderly worker who was sitting on a couch playing with his phone. I walked around and found someone and asked if we could get some help and he said “hold on let me find someone.” He goes and finds the phone dude on the couch who saunters on over to us. We tell him we want this mattress and he spends 15 min checking tags and prices and then tries to talk us into another mattress. I tell him no, we want the one we picked. He spends more time checking prices and finally tells us how much it will be. We’re cool with it and tell him we want it. He tells us it won’t be available to be picked up at the warehouse for another 2 weeks. A bit inconvenient, but we still go ahead and purchase it. Two weeks later and the mattress is ready to be picked up from the warehouse. My husband goes to get it and brings it home only to find out it’s not the right mattress! He drives back to this Ashley store to be told that yes it is indeed the wrong mattress. The mattress that we wanted is discontinued and they can’t sell us the floor model. So now here we are two weeks later with the wrong mattress and can’t even get the correct one. I feel in this situation, someone from the store should come and pick it up from our house since 1. This is their fault and 2. Spending an entire day driving all over town with this mattress is a huge inconvenience. My husband and I are extremely upset about the whole situation but nothing got done to make it right in the end. Definitely won’t be finding another mattress or any other furniture here in the future.

Shavone Thomas was amazing to work with, excellent customer service. I was not excited to have to buy a new bed and was not looking forward to the hunt or the negotiation back and forth. I visted Ashley on a random Thursday and Shavone approached us right away but was not pushy at all. I was quite impressed with several bedroom sets and he went around and let us examine them all. He then ran total prices on three different sets so I could see the differences. I wanted to think on it a bit and he was not pushy at all. Gave me his card with cell # and said "let me know if you decided to come back." I found the same set I liked most for less on an online site and he worked with me to match it before I came back in to purchase. The process was much less troubling than I expected. He is very personable and accommodating.
